:INFO
Axolotl Daily and Weekly Care Routine
Consistent care prevents most health issues. Water quality is the single most important factor in axolotl health. Test before medicating.

:TASK
[ ] Daily: check temperature and confirm it is under 18 Celsius
[ ] Daily: observe the axolotl for normal posture and gill plume appearance
[ ] Daily: remove any uneaten food within 60 minutes of feeding
[ ] Weekly: test ammonia, nitrite, nitrate, and pH with a liquid test kit
[ ] Weekly: perform a 20 to 30 percent water change with dechlorinated water
[ ] Monthly: rinse sponge filter in tank water (never tap water)
[ ] Monthly: check for signs of fungus (white fluffy growths on gills or skin)

:NOTE
Gill shrinkage is a sign of poor water quality or stress before visible illness. Improve water conditions first and monitor before taking further action.
